11/12/2006
KALOTINA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev reopened the modernised Kalotina crossing at the border with Serbia on Monday (December 11th), which has been equipped with special inspection checkpoints for veterinary control. 
Following its EU entry on January 1st, Bulgaria will serve as an external border of the Union.
In other news, Bulgaria observed a day of mourning Sunday for the victims of the bus crash last week that killed 18 people near Byala. 
Interior Minister Rumen Petkov announced that a dangerous section of road over the Yantra River would be replaced with a new bridge. 
(Bulgarian Government website, Monitor - 11/12/06; Darik, Mediapool - 10/12/06)
